  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "BAJAJ picked as \u2018Most Loved Motorcycle Brand\u2019 for 4th consecutive year",
      "author": "Thilina Walpola",
      "body_lines": [
        "For the fourth consecutive year, Bajaj was picked as the \u201cMost Loved Motorcycle Brand\u201d and placed among the top 50 most loved brands in Sri Lanka by LMD \u2013 Brand Finance Awards 2022 in the 19th edition of its annual review.The Bajaj brand has been recognised by Brand Finance Lanka in their annual reviews since 2011 and with the introduction of this category as the \u2018Most Loved Motorcycle Brand\u2019 in 2019, 2020, 2021 and 2022.",
        "Lakmal De Silva, Deputy General Manager (Vehicle Sales), DPMC said; \u201cOur 360-degree commitment to the brand including superior, accessible after-sales service is key for the Bajaj brand securing the \u2018Most Loved Motorcycle Brand\u2019 title, even though at the time of the award brand new motorcycles had not been available in the country for over 2 years.\u201d",
        "To meet the brand loyal Bajaj consumers\u2019 need for brand-new motorcycles, recently David Pieris Motor Company (Private) Limited (DPMC) reintroduced the Bajaj CT 100, with local value addition under the Standard Operating Procedure\u00a0for Automobile Manufacturing/ Assembling Industry and Automobile Component Manufacturing Industry in Sri Lanka introduced by the Ministry of Industries.The Bajaj CT 100, one of the bestselling bikes in the Bajaj family is renowned for its fuel efficiency, durability, and performance which also makes it the ideal vehicle in the current economic environment.",
        "PickMe proposes fuel supply for passenger transportation via a digital pool",
